text.tspan: Prevalence of developmental intellectual disability in males vs. females, 2019
Share of males versus females with 'idiopathic developmental intellectual disability', which is a category of disorders defined by delayed or
impaired speech, language, motor condition, and visuo-spatial skills. Prevalence has been age-standardized to compare between countries
Data source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019)
